<p>The Elm Grove estate is a small estate situated behind Sutton High street. It comprises approximately two-dozen blocks of two or three-storey terraced housing and maisonettes. In 2018, the site was designated for redevelopment in the Councilâ€™s Local plan (site STC45).</p>

<p>The estate is one of seven estates listed in <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MdX6GlaHDoBdG6CTsvjFaIuPtIa9id5O/view">Suttonâ€™s Local Plan (2018)</a> for potential redevelopment.</p>

<p>The Council has set up a steering group to represent residents on the estate, which is <a href="https://www.sutton.gov.uk/info/200502/housing_advice_and_options/1659/elm_grove/6">currently in the process of appointing an independent tenant advisor</a> in anticipation of drawing up plans for the redevelopment and holding a ballot.</p>

